## 1. Structural Design Philosophy

- Keep the structural concept conservative, simple, inspectable, and compatible with mountain terrain.
- Favor clear load paths, robust moisture separation, reliable drainage, and buildable interfaces between structure, terrace, roof, and envelope.
- Treat the large panoramic terrace, large glazing, snow exposure, wind exposure, frost, slope, and site access as primary risk drivers.
- Use this document to brief licensed professionals, not to size or approve structural members.

## 2. Required Geotechnical Investigation

