## 6. Drainage Strategy

- Drainage must move water away from foundations, slab edges, retaining elements, terrace waterproofing, and access paths.
- Mountain slope runoff and terrace runoff must be handled as coordinated civil/architectural/structural design issues.
- Drainage elements may include perimeter drains, free-draining gravel, positive falls, swales, gutters, downpipes, and controlled discharge points.
- Final drainage design requires site survey and authority review.

## 7. Ground Slab Concept

- Ground slab should be coordinated with bearing conditions, insulation, vapor control, radon/local requirements, underfloor heating, floor drains, and thresholds.
