## 20. Structural Engineer Review Checklist

- Confirm geotechnical investigation scope and design parameters.
- Confirm gravity load path, lateral system, diaphragm strategy, and foundation concept.
- Confirm snow, wind, seismic, terrace, guard, roof, and glazing support assumptions.
- Confirm variant selection and whether timber hybrid, CLT/glulam, or masonry hybrid is appropriate.
- Confirm all member sizes, connections, anchorage, reinforcement, bracing, and temporary works.
- Confirm moisture, condensation, durability, fire, acoustic, and construction sequencing implications.
- Confirm that no generated document is used as a final calculation, reinforcement drawing, permit approval, or safety-compliance certificate.

